Add unit tests for the `<relay_context>` filter fixes (tasks 2.1 and 2.2) to the transcript parser and reader test suites.

**Context:** Tests for transcript-parser live at `apps/server/src/services/__tests__/transcript-parser.test.ts` (verify with glob if path differs). Tests for transcript-reader live at `apps/server/src/services/__tests__/transcript-reader.test.ts`. Both test files should have tests that confirm relay metadata is stripped.

**Implementation steps:**

1. Locate or confirm the path of the transcript-parser test file. Add the following test:

```typescript
it('filters relay_context blocks from parsed messages', () => {
  // Purpose: confirm relay metadata never reaches the chat UI
  const lines = [
    JSON.stringify({
      type: 'user',
      uuid: 'u1',
      message: {
        role: 'user',
        content: '<relay_context>\nAgent-ID: abc\nHops: 1\n</relay_context>'
      }
    }),
    JSON.stringify({
      type: 'assistant',
      uuid: 'a1',
      message: {
        role: 'assistant',
        content: [{ type: 'text', text: 'Done' }]
      }
    }),
  ];

  const messages = parseTranscript(lines);

  const userMessages = messages.filter((m) => m.role === 'user');
  expect(userMessages).toHaveLength(0); // relay_context line is filtered out
  const assistantMessages = messages.filter((m) => m.role === 'assistant');
  expect(assistantMessages).toHaveLength(1); // assistant still present
  expect(assistantMessages[0].content).toBe('Done');
});

it('does not filter regular user messages starting with other prefixes', () => {
  const lines = [
    JSON.stringify({
      type: 'user',
      uuid: 'u1',
      message: { role: 'user', content: 'Hello world' }
    }),
  ];
  const messages = parseTranscript(lines);
  expect(messages).toHaveLength(1);
  expect(messages[0].content).toBe('Hello world');
});
```

