Add a unit test for the TanStack Query cache merge fix (task 2.3) to `use-session-status.test.ts`, and update `contributing/architecture.md` to document the two behavioral changes introduced by this spec.

**Part A: Client test**

Locate or create `apps/client/src/layers/entities/session/model/__tests__/use-session-status.test.ts`. Add the following test:

```typescript
/**
 * @vitest-environment jsdom
 */
import { describe, it, expect, vi, beforeEach } from 'vitest';
import { renderHook, act, waitFor } from '@testing-library/react';
import { QueryClient, QueryClientProvider } from '@tanstack/react-query';
import { useSessionStatus } from '../use-session-status';
import { TransportProvider } from '@/layers/shared/model';
import { createMockTransport } from '@dorkos/test-utils';

describe('useSessionStatus', () => {
  let queryClient: QueryClient;
  let mockTransport: ReturnType<typeof createMockTransport>;

  beforeEach(() => {
    queryClient = new QueryClient({ defaultOptions: { queries: { retry: false } } });
    mockTransport = createMockTransport();
  });

  function Wrapper({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) {
    return (
      <QueryClientProvider client={queryClient}>
        <TransportProvider transport={mockTransport}>
          {children}
        </TransportProvider>
      </QueryClientProvider>
    );
  }

  it('preserves existing permissionMode when updating model', async () => {
    // Purpose: prove the merge strategy prevents cross-field reset
    const { result } = renderHook(
      () => useSessionStatus('session-1', null, false),
      { wrapper: Wrapper }
    );

    // Prime cache with both fields set
    act(() => {
      queryClient.setQueryData(['session', 'session-1', undefined], {
        id: 'session-1',
        model: 'claude-haiku-4-5',
        permissionMode: 'acceptEdits',
        title: 'Test',
        createdAt: new Date().toISOString(),
        updatedAt: new Date().toISOString(),
      });
    });

    // Server returns only the updated model field
    vi.mocked(mockTransport.updateSession).mockResolvedValue({
      id: 'session-1',
      model: 'claude-opus-4-6',
      title: 'Test',
      createdAt: new Date().toISOString(),
      updatedAt: new Date().toISOString(),
    });

    await act(async () => {
      await result.current.updateSession({ model: 'claude-opus-4-6' });
    });

    const cached = queryClient.getQueryData(['session', 'session-1', undefined]) as Record<string, unknown>;
    expect(cached?.model).toBe('claude-opus-4-6');
    expect(cached?.permissionMode).toBe('acceptEdits'); // must be preserved
  });

  it('preserves existing model when updating permissionMode', async () => {
    const { result } = renderHook(
      () => useSessionStatus('session-2', null, false),
      { wrapper: Wrapper }
    );

    act(() => {
      queryClient.setQueryData(['session', 'session-2', undefined], {
        id: 'session-2',
        model: 'claude-opus-4-6',
        permissionMode: 'default',
        title: 'Test 2',
        createdAt: new Date().toISOString(),
        updatedAt: new Date().toISOString(),
      });
    });

    vi.mocked(mockTransport.updateSession).mockResolvedValue({
      id: 'session-2',
      permissionMode: 'acceptEdits',
      title: 'Test 2',
      createdAt: new Date().toISOString(),
      updatedAt: new Date().toISOString(),
    });

    await act(async () => {
      await result.current.updateSession({ permissionMode: 'acceptEdits' });
    });

    const cached = queryClient.getQueryData(['session', 'session-2', undefined]) as Record<string, unknown>;
    expect(cached?.permissionMode).toBe('acceptEdits');
    expect(cached?.model).toBe('claude-opus-4-6'); // must be preserved
  });
});
```

**Part B: Architecture documentation**

Open `contributing/architecture.md`. Find the section that describes `sendSSEEvent` (likely under the Server section or SSE Streaming Protocol). Add a note:

> `sendSSEEvent` is async and must be awaited at all call sites. It awaits Node's `drain` event when `res.write()` returns `false` (socket buffer full) to prevent SSE stream stalls on long responses. Forgetting `await` causes backpressure to be silently ignored.

Also find the GET /api/sessions/:id/messages description and add:

> Before reading the JSONL transcript, the handler calls `agentManager.getSdkSessionId(id)` to translate the client-facing session ID to the SDK-assigned JSONL filename. This handles the case where the URL still holds the original DorkOS UUID from session creation. Falls back to the URL parameter if no translation is found (sessions loaded from disk already use the correct SDK UUID).

**Acceptance criteria:**
- `preserves existing permissionMode when updating model` test: after calling `updateSession({ model })`, cache entry still has `permissionMode: 'acceptEdits'`.
- `preserves existing model when updating permissionMode` test: after calling `updateSession({ permissionMode })`, cache entry still has `model: 'claude-opus-4-6'`.
- Both tests pass with `pnpm vitest run`.
- `contributing/architecture.md` contains the note about `sendSSEEvent` being async.
- `contributing/architecture.md` contains the note about session ID translation in GET /messages.
